	Sharapova pulls out   
	Montreal: World No. 3 Maria Sharapova pulled out of the Beijing Olympics on Thursday after an MRI scan on her right shoulder revealed two small tears.  
	The Russian was examined by doctors after withdrawing from the Montreal Cup late on Wednesday evening with a sore shoulder following a 7-5, 5-7, 6-2 win over Polands Marta Domachowska. After yesterdays match, I knew there was something seriously wrong with my shoulder, she said.         
	Yelena denial         
	 Moscow: Yelena Soboleva denied on Friday she had manipulated her doping samples after the world indoor 1,500m champion and six other leading Russian women athletes were banned ahead of the Beijing Olympics.         
	Thanou angry         
	 Athens: Greek sprinter Katerina Thanou has slammed the International Olympic Committees (IOC) decision to delay a hearing on her participation in the Beijing Games until the eve of the opening ceremony.         
